Ok I propose to wait until Wednesday before ping laanwj for merging if he agrees.

@EricLarch The clock is ticking :)

@Thashiznets I initially flagged French because the first [test vector](https://github.com/simcity4242/pybitcointools/blob/master/test_bip39.py) contains "abandon" (11/12 words) and my code was just checking the first word (like Electrum), so the English test vectors were returning "French" as language; I've used a [workaround](https://github.com/simcity4242/pybitcointools/blob/master/bitcoin/mnemonic.py#L45)

Basically, I've been trying to differentiate mnemonic phrases without needing to know if it's BIP39, or Electrum 2.x (or Electrum 1.x, which is much harder). I just think it's prudent to have certainty in knowing what type of mnemonic it is by the words alone. 

My reasoning also extends to [this](http://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/a/38027/9382) (which @gurnec answered).
